OL,3,C'Significant failures' in policing led
OL,4,Cto violent disorder, report finds
OL,6,FMeanwhile, the Chief Superintendent of
OL,7,FLeicestershire Police, Shane O'Neill,
OL,8,Fsaid: "The disorder, tensions and
OL,9,Funrest that occurred in East Leicester
OL,10,Fduring September 2022 represented an
OL,11,Fexceptionally complex and challenging
OL,12,Fperiod. The impact was felt not only
OL,13,Facross our diverse city, but also by
OL,14,Fcommunities beyond Leicester.
OL,16,F"Leicestershire Police has fully
OL,17,Fengaged with and supported the
OL,18,FGovernment's Independent Review, which
OL,19,Fhas not yet been published.
OL,26,@pD@GOUxD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,375,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F374A1771876127
OL,3,C'Significant failures' in policing led
OL,4,Cto violent disorder, report finds
OL,6,F"We will, of course, carefully
OL,7,Fconsider the findings of this review
OL,8,Fwhen it is published on Monday 23
OL,9,FFebruary, as part of our ongoing
OL,10,Fcommitment to learning and
OL,11,Fimprovement."
OL,13,F"We remain committed to supporting
OL,14,Fboth established and emerging
OL,15,Fcommunities across Leicester,
OL,16,FLeicestershire, and Rutland.
OL,26,@sD@MO]uD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G7/9
